title: Whitewater runs in 78th Midwest Invite
text:
Senior Sarah Ziolkowski’s Top 25 finish led the Whitewater girls’ cross country team to an 18th-place finish in the 78th annual Janesville Midwest Invitational, held Saturday at Blackhawk Golf Course. 
Ziolkowski’s 5,000-meter time of 20:02.56 placed her 23rd in a field that featured 217 runners. 
“This was a solid race for her and she is hungry for more,” said Whitewater coach Chad Carstens of Ziolkowski. 
Senior Andrea Sandoval earned a Top 50 finish, running a 20:54.64 to place 48th. 
“Andrea Sandoval raced well through the crowd almost equaling her time on a hot day at the Verona Invite several weeks ago. This also is a good confidence booster for her as she gets comfortable with racing again,” said Carstens. 
Brody Runez earned a 56th-place finish to lead the Whippet boys. Runez ran a 17:09.37. 
“Although finishing 56th, he is doing quite well in his first season on the team as a junior. His time of 17:09 is something to be proud of but also to look to build on as the season rolls on,” Carstens said of Runez. 
Whitewater competes again today in the Rock Valley North Divisional Championship at the Timber Lee Christian Center hosted by East Troy.
